question.title: why does jpa query the same column multiple times when using a one to many relationship?

node.contents: Why would this query generate duplicates? Side notes: if you used an autogenerated, single-column ID, you wouldn't have the problem. And it would be easier to have the mapping right. Your mapping is wrong: The OneToMany association should use the mappedBy attribute, to be marked as the inverse side of the ManyToOne in Permission. And it shouldn't be annotated with JoinColumn.

node.contents: The Permission entity should have an auto-generated, single-column ID. In fact, all your entities should. It would be more efficient, easier to code, easier to map, no need for PK classes with potentially buggy equals and hashCodes, clean URLs with a single parameter to refer to a given permission by ID...
